00:00:06.741 --> 00:00:07.575 position:38% line:89% align:start
[beeping]

00:00:12.747 --> 00:00:14.716 position:7% line:83% align:start
[researcher] He's currently in
a deep REM sleep,

00:00:14.749 --> 00:00:16.784 position:13% line:89% align:start
and has been for some time.

00:00:19.152 --> 00:00:21.990 position:16% line:83% align:start
He woke up in the posture
like an ascetic monk.

00:00:22.022 --> 00:00:24.959 position:19% line:83% align:start
And when it seemed like
he might be awake,

00:00:24.993 --> 00:00:27.094 position:21% line:83% align:start
he went back to sleep
for 24 hours.

00:00:27.762 --> 00:00:29.096 position:33% line:89% align:start
Makes sense,

00:00:29.129 --> 00:00:31.566 position:16% line:83% align:start
since he has zero memory
to speak of.

00:00:31.599 --> 00:00:33.501 position:16% line:83% align:start
How are his learning and
cognitive skills

00:00:33.535 --> 00:00:34.802 position:21% line:89% align:start
after being revived?

00:00:34.836 --> 00:00:36.470 position:24% line:89% align:start
They're all normal.

00:00:36.504 --> 00:00:38.272 position:24% line:83% align:start
He's even memorized
30 English words.

00:00:39.007 --> 00:00:41.275 position:16% line:83% align:start
However, he doesn't seem
to know

00:00:41.308 --> 00:00:43.143 position:19% line:83% align:start
or understand his name
as Jotaro Cujoh.

00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:47.314 position:24% line:89% align:start
As for his family,

00:00:47.347 --> 00:00:50.150 position:7% line:83% align:start
he shows no reaction, not even
to a picture of his daughter.

00:00:55.924 --> 00:00:58.158 position:30% line:83% align:start
His EEG and EKG
read as normal, too.

00:00:58.191 --> 00:01:02.496 position:13% line:83% align:start
However, his muscle values
are on the decline.

00:01:02.530 --> 00:01:03.998 position:24% line:83% align:start
Having no memories
would indicate

00:01:04.032 --> 00:01:06.166 position:21% line:83% align:start
that he naturally has
no motivation

00:01:06.199 --> 00:01:09.436 position:30% line:83% align:start
to go on living
as the mind is shutting down.

00:01:09.469 --> 00:01:13.473 position:7% line:83% align:start
In response, the muscles begin
to deteriorate quickly.

00:01:14.308 --> 00:01:17.110 position:24% line:83% align:start
All right, doctor.
What's the plan?

00:01:18.145 --> 00:01:19.446 position:27% line:89% align:start
I don't know yet.

00:01:19.479 --> 00:01:21.348 position:35% line:83% align:start
We may have
no other choice here

00:01:21.381 --> 00:01:23.283 position:24% line:83% align:start
than to try and get
his memories back.

00:01:23.985 --> 00:01:24.786 position:24% line:89% align:start
[researcher gasps]

00:01:25.653 --> 00:01:27.989 position:33% line:83% align:start
Doctor, wait!
Don't touch his head!

00:01:28.022 --> 00:01:28.790 position:27% line:89% align:start
[glass shatters]

00:01:31.059 --> 00:01:33.528 position:33% line:83% align:start
He's injured!
Get him some first aid!

00:01:33.561 --> 00:01:38.332 position:10% line:83% align:start
I apologize, doctor. I forgot
to warn you about that before.

00:01:38.365 --> 00:01:40.568 position:24% line:83% align:start
Did he just release
his Stand power?

00:01:40.602 --> 00:01:43.972 position:13% line:83% align:start
Yes! However, it's actually
not from his memory,

00:01:44.005 --> 00:01:45.873 position:35% line:83% align:start
but rather
an instinct of defense.

00:01:50.011 --> 00:01:52.145 position:24% line:89% align:start
It says "Jo...lyne"

00:01:52.780 --> 00:01:53.848 position:30% line:89% align:start
Wait! "Jolyne"?

00:01:54.716 --> 00:01:54.882 position:35% line:89% align:start
No! No way!

00:01:57.184 --> 00:01:58.385 position:16% line:89% align:start
It couldn't possibly say!

00:01:59.219 --> 00:02:00.187 position:19% line:89% align:start
[pensive music playing]

00:02:08.195 --> 00:02:09.363 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Jotaro] I want you to know...

00:02:10.598 --> 00:02:12.066 position:24% line:89% align:start
I want you to know

00:02:12.100 --> 00:02:15.503 position:16% line:83% align:start
you are always incredibly
important to me.

00:02:18.238 --> 00:02:21.375 position:35% line:83% align:start
Holy shit!
Look at the wounds on your arm.

00:02:21.408 --> 00:02:25.212 position:13% line:83% align:start
Even though I treated them,
even though I healed them.

00:02:26.614 --> 00:02:28.916 position:13% line:83% align:start
They've formed shapes that
spell something out. Clearly.

00:02:30.752 --> 00:02:31.919 position:10% line:89% align:start
I'll try healing them again.

00:02:32.587 --> 00:02:33.521 position:38% line:89% align:start
No! Wait!

00:02:34.254 --> 00:02:35.757 position:7% line:89% align:start
I don't want you to heal this.

00:02:37.091 --> 00:02:38.559 position:21% line:89% align:start
[F.F. exhales softly]

00:02:38.593 --> 00:02:40.862 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Jolyne] I have no way
to explain it,

00:02:40.895 --> 00:02:41.896 position:33% line:89% align:start
but I know...

00:02:42.997 --> 00:02:45.633 position:21% line:83% align:start
This is... a message
sent from my dad.

00:02:47.434 --> 00:02:48.636 position:10% line:89% align:start
Since before I was even born,

00:02:48.670 --> 00:02:52.507 position:27% line:83% align:start
that man has been
watching over so many things.

00:02:52.540 --> 00:02:54.374 position:24% line:83% align:start
To keep Mama and I
from being involved

00:02:54.408 --> 00:02:56.044 position:21% line:83% align:start
in scenarios exactly
like the ones

00:02:56.077 --> 00:02:57.645 position:10% line:89% align:start
that are going on right now.

00:02:57.679 --> 00:02:59.547 position:21% line:83% align:start
He made sure to keep
his distance,

00:02:59.580 --> 00:03:00.313 position:19% line:83% align:start
knowing that'd help me
stay safe.

00:03:02.750 --> 00:03:05.787 position:16% line:89% align:start
Yes, just now, I felt it.

00:03:05.820 --> 00:03:09.456 position:7% line:83% align:start
I believe that through my body,
my dad speaks to me.

00:04:45.219 --> 00:04:47.588 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Hey, F.F.
-What?

00:04:47.622 --> 00:04:50.390 position:16% line:83% align:start
So, could you maybe hook
Jolyne's leg on the stairs?

00:04:50.423 --> 00:04:53.360 position:13% line:83% align:start
That'll make her slow down
a little bit and trip.

00:04:54.061 --> 00:04:56.164 position:13% line:89% align:start
You want me to do what now?

00:04:56.197 --> 00:04:57.430 position:33% line:89% align:start
Like I said,

00:04:57.464 --> 00:04:58.365 position:24% line:83% align:start
I want her to trip,
but it's not what you think.

00:05:00.168 --> 00:05:02.003 position:13% line:83% align:start
I won't actually allow her
to fall down.

00:05:02.837 --> 00:05:04.806 position:24% line:83% align:start
You see, as soon as
she stumbles,

00:05:04.839 --> 00:05:06.808 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'm going to catch her
in my arms.

00:05:06.841 --> 00:05:07.708 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:05:08.209 --> 00:05:10.011 position:24% line:89% align:start
The thing is she...

00:05:10.044 --> 00:05:11.646 position:16% line:89% align:start
might not understand that

00:05:11.679 --> 00:05:14.615 position:16% line:83% align:start
she was protected earlier
because of me.

00:05:14.649 --> 00:05:18.451 position:10% line:83% align:start
What I desire is to feel her
in my embrace again.

00:05:18.485 --> 00:05:20.788 position:27% line:89% align:start
So, go do it now!

00:05:20.822 --> 00:05:23.291 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Come on! Just trip her.
-Sexual harassment and assault?

00:05:23.323 --> 00:05:24.659 position:21% line:89% align:start
That's on you, buddy.

00:05:24.692 --> 00:05:28.229 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'll tell you again. I'm going
to make Jolyne my wife.

00:05:28.262 --> 00:05:30.531 position:27% line:83% align:start
And you are going
to help me with that.

00:05:30.565 --> 00:05:33.366 position:13% line:83% align:start
Are you the sort of person
who breaks their promises?

00:05:34.135 --> 00:05:35.036 position:44% line:89% align:start
Ugh!

00:05:37.370 --> 00:05:39.807 position:35% line:89% align:start
Now, do it!

00:05:39.841 --> 00:05:40.373 position:33% line:89% align:start
[F.F. sighs]

00:05:41.709 --> 00:05:44.011 position:16% line:83% align:start
[F.F.] I'm sorry, Jolyne,
but I have to.

00:05:46.781 --> 00:05:47.380 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:05:47.414 --> 00:05:49.250 position:19% line:89% align:start
I caught the small man!

00:05:49.283 --> 00:05:50.518 position:27% line:83% align:start
He must have been
spying on us

00:05:50.551 --> 00:05:52.553 position:21% line:83% align:start
from the floor above
the whole time.

00:05:54.689 --> 00:05:57.892 position:13% line:83% align:start
That's it! He's holding the
bone in his hand, right there!

00:05:57.925 --> 00:05:59.760 position:30% line:89% align:start
[man mumbling]

00:06:02.063 --> 00:06:02.730 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:06:06.067 --> 00:06:07.367 position:27% line:89% align:start
[groans in pain]

00:06:07.400 --> 00:06:08.368 position:21% line:89% align:start
[F.F.] Oh, he sure is

00:06:08.401 --> 00:06:10.271 position:16% line:83% align:start
a slippery little fucker,
isn't he?

00:06:10.304 --> 00:06:12.073 position:19% line:89% align:start
But he won't escape me!

00:06:12.405 --> 00:06:14.075 position:38% line:89% align:start
No! Wait!

00:06:14.108 --> 00:06:16.210 position:27% line:83% align:start
Something's wrong
with his back.

00:06:16.244 --> 00:06:17.578 position:21% line:89% align:start
[mumbling continues]

00:06:21.649 --> 00:06:24.451 position:21% line:83% align:start
You said earlier that
he was a small man, right?

00:06:24.484 --> 00:06:26.954 position:38% line:83% align:start
He indeed
fit that category before.

00:06:26.988 --> 00:06:30.758 position:16% line:83% align:start
-But now, he's somehow...
-[man] Sunbathing...

00:06:30.791 --> 00:06:33.361 position:19% line:83% align:start
...getting much taller
before our eyes.

00:06:33.393 --> 00:06:36.998 position:30% line:83% align:start
As tall as me.
No, even taller, in fact.

00:06:37.031 --> 00:06:39.600 position:21% line:83% align:start
Hey, you're cornered.
No more running away!

00:06:39.634 --> 00:06:41.602 position:13% line:89% align:start
Now, face me nice and slow.

00:06:42.435 --> 00:06:44.739 position:7% line:89% align:start
[man] Feels good... The sun...

00:06:44.772 --> 00:06:45.973 position:33% line:89% align:start
The light...

00:06:46.007 --> 00:06:48.776 position:16% line:83% align:start
Hey, I'm talking to you,
asshole. Look at me!

00:06:50.678 --> 00:06:51.478 position:44% line:89% align:start
Grrr.

00:06:52.680 --> 00:06:54.949 position:38% line:89% align:start
Agh, agh!

00:06:55.383 --> 00:06:55.950 position:35% line:89% align:start
[all gasp]

00:06:57.184 --> 00:06:58.819 position:41% line:89% align:start
Bleh...

00:07:02.455 --> 00:07:04.125 position:13% line:89% align:start
What's wrong with this guy?

00:07:04.158 --> 00:07:08.963 position:7% line:89% align:start
[man] Light is... bleh... warm.

00:07:08.996 --> 00:07:14.602 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's very lively. Everyone
gathers here and it's so warm.

00:07:15.336 --> 00:07:16.003 position:44% line:89% align:start
Bleh.

00:07:16.604 --> 00:07:18.606 position:30% line:89% align:start
[ominous music]

00:07:22.643 --> 00:07:23.778 position:21% line:89% align:start
[F.F.] What the hell?

00:07:23.811 --> 00:07:25.179 position:24% line:83% align:start
His head literally
just exploded.

00:07:25.212 --> 00:07:27.648 position:33% line:83% align:start
Do you think
he's a Stand User?

00:07:27.682 --> 00:07:29.550 position:24% line:83% align:start
Just stay away. No,
it doesn't look like a Stand.

00:07:31.185 --> 00:07:32.485 position:16% line:89% align:start
I don't know what it is,

00:07:32.520 --> 00:07:34.487 position:24% line:83% align:start
but whatever we do,
we shouldn't touch him.

00:07:34.522 --> 00:07:36.456 position:41% line:83% align:start
[gasps]
Shit! Where'd the bone go?

00:07:37.158 --> 00:07:37.959 position:13% line:89% align:start
He was holding it earlier.

00:07:37.992 --> 00:07:39.860 position:30% line:83% align:start
What happened?
We have to find it.

00:07:40.294 --> 00:07:42.029 position:35% line:89% align:start
[all gasp]

00:07:56.344 --> 00:07:57.578 position:35% line:89% align:start
Holy crap!

00:07:57.611 --> 00:07:59.647 position:30% line:83% align:start
It's happening
to the other inmates, too?

00:08:01.315 --> 00:08:04.685 position:13% line:83% align:start
They're undeniably turning
into plants.

00:08:04.719 --> 00:08:06.887 position:21% line:83% align:start
They appear to still
be growing, too.

00:08:06.921 --> 00:08:08.089 position:16% line:83% align:start
But why? What's happening
to them all?

00:08:08.122 --> 00:08:09.557 position:16% line:89% align:start
Who could have done this?

00:08:11.425 --> 00:08:12.593 position:21% line:83% align:start
What possible reason
could anyone have?

00:08:16.697 --> 00:08:18.733 position:13% line:83% align:start
[D an' G] Perhaps, I should
think of this

00:08:18.766 --> 00:08:20.701 position:16% line:89% align:start
as a Stand power as well.

00:08:21.402 --> 00:08:23.004 position:33% line:89% align:start
Of the bone.

00:08:23.037 --> 00:08:26.207 position:13% line:83% align:start
It seems like the power and
will fueling this phenomenon,

00:08:26.240 --> 00:08:27.808 position:13% line:89% align:start
is, in so doing, attempting

00:08:27.842 --> 00:08:29.910 position:16% line:83% align:start
to give life to something
entirely new.

00:08:30.344 --> 00:08:32.046 position:30% line:89% align:start
Flowers bloom,

00:08:32.079 --> 00:08:35.182 position:16% line:83% align:start
as well as stems, leaves,
even a tiny little trunk.

00:08:35.783 --> 00:08:37.952 position:16% line:89% align:start
And at the end of that...

00:08:37.985 --> 00:08:39.053 position:35% line:83% align:start
Well then,
what should I do with

00:08:39.086 --> 00:08:42.156 position:33% line:83% align:start
the bone that
the small man dropped?

00:08:42.189 --> 00:08:44.959 position:21% line:89% align:start
This is a conundrum.

00:08:44.992 --> 00:08:47.361 position:7% line:83% align:start
I now know that it's dangerous
to touch the bone.

00:08:47.395 --> 00:08:50.331 position:27% line:83% align:start
To say nothing of
touching anyone else

00:08:50.364 --> 00:08:51.932 position:19% line:83% align:start
who's come into contact
with it.

00:08:51.966 --> 00:08:53.334 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Anastasia gasps]

00:08:53.367 --> 00:08:56.037 position:7% line:83% align:start
Stop right there, Jolyne Cujoh!
Don't go any further!

00:08:56.070 --> 00:08:57.204 position:24% line:89% align:start
I told you to stop!

00:08:57.238 --> 00:08:59.907 position:13% line:89% align:start
[suspenseful music playing]

00:09:00.574 --> 00:09:02.376 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:09:02.410 --> 00:09:03.744 position:13% line:89% align:start
Turn around and look at me.

00:09:04.545 --> 00:09:05.913 position:10% line:89% align:start
I want to see your face now.

00:09:10.818 --> 00:09:13.587 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Okay?
-That's good?

00:09:13.621 --> 00:09:16.057 position:27% line:83% align:start
Just stay there!
I need to check something.

00:09:21.595 --> 00:09:23.064 position:30% line:89% align:start
[grunts softly]

00:09:23.097 --> 00:09:24.665 position:35% line:89% align:start
[sniffs]

00:09:24.698 --> 00:09:26.233 position:41% line:83% align:start
[gasps]
Hey! Are you out of your mind?

00:09:26.267 --> 00:09:27.536 position:27% line:89% align:start
Get away from me!

00:09:27.568 --> 00:09:29.504 position:19% line:89% align:start
Anastasia! You pervert!

00:09:29.538 --> 00:09:31.772 position:30% line:83% align:start
Be quiet, F.F.!
I'm doing this for a reason.

00:09:31.806 --> 00:09:33.707 position:21% line:83% align:start
All the prisoners at
this Discipline Ward

00:09:33.741 --> 00:09:36.077 position:21% line:83% align:start
became like this due
to the bone.

00:09:36.110 --> 00:09:37.311 position:16% line:89% align:start
It's not an enemy Stand.

00:09:38.145 --> 00:09:39.747 position:16% line:83% align:start
The enemy would have used
their power

00:09:39.780 --> 00:09:42.016 position:24% line:83% align:start
to attack us first
if that were true.

00:09:42.049 --> 00:09:45.820 position:33% line:83% align:start
Also, Jolyne,
I thought that a bit earlier,

00:09:45.853 --> 00:09:47.655 position:16% line:83% align:start
with your thread looking
the way it did

00:09:47.688 --> 00:09:48.422 position:7% line:89% align:start
that you had touched the bone.

00:09:48.456 --> 00:09:50.191 position:19% line:89% align:start
Am I right about that?

00:09:50.559 --> 00:09:51.258 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:09:54.795 --> 00:10:00.267 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm!

00:10:00.301 --> 00:10:00.935 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne gasps]

00:10:02.203 --> 00:10:04.638 position:10% line:89% align:start
The bone! It's rolling away!

00:10:05.005 --> 00:10:05.606 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:10:07.408 --> 00:10:10.611 position:44% line:83% align:start
Shit!
You've been infected, Jolyne.

00:10:10.644 --> 00:10:11.812 position:16% line:89% align:start
[dramatic music playing]

00:10:13.347 --> 00:10:13.647 position:33% line:89% align:start
The hell, no!

00:10:17.351 --> 00:10:18.819 position:33% line:89% align:start
Diver Drive!

00:10:19.987 --> 00:10:22.289 position:27% line:89% align:start
[F.F.] Nice one!

00:10:22.323 --> 00:10:24.391 position:7% line:83% align:start
Anastasia, want to hurry it up?
Yank it all out from inside.

00:10:25.726 --> 00:10:28.629 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[Jolyne gasps]
-Wait! You're not finished yet?

00:10:28.662 --> 00:10:29.964 position:24% line:89% align:start
It's still growing.

00:10:29.997 --> 00:10:31.765 position:24% line:83% align:start
It's not correct or
proper to say

00:10:31.799 --> 00:10:34.603 position:27% line:83% align:start
